  {
    "type": "EXPOSITORY (ENGLISH BIBLE)",
    "name": "Benson Commentary",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "bld",
        "text": "Exodus 31:14-16",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "verse-link",
            "text": "Exodus 31:14-16",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "It is holy unto you — ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "That is, it is designed for your benefit as well as for God’s honour; it shall be accounted holy by you. It is the ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "sabbath of rest, holy to the Lord — ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "It is separated from common use to the service of God; and by the observance of it we are taught to rest from worldly pursuits, and devote ourselves, and all we are, have, and can do, to God’s glory. It was to be observed throughout their generations, in every age, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "for a perpetual covenant — ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "This was to be one of the most lasting tokens of the covenant between God and Israel.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "p",
        "text": "",
        "children": [
